I would like to propose an alternative usage to `<script src="https://code.jquery.com/jquery-migrate-3.0.1.js"></script>`:   Make jquery-migrate npm package that appears to be identical to jquery.  This way, I don't need to change any `require('jquery')` or webpack settings in a complex project, but only change the package.json:

```yaml
{
  "dependencies": {
    // this could be a link to a .gz NPM package file, etc
    "jquery": "git+https://github.com/jquery/jquery-migrate.git"
  }
}
```

An (yarn-only) alternative is to use package aliasing, https://twitter.com/sebmck/status/873958247304232961?lang=en -- too bad NPM doesn't support it.

